Ile Louët is perched in Morlaix Bay in Brittany and is the perfect retreat for up to 10 guests for the price of €200 (£145) for two nights . 
  The lighthouse keeper's cottage was used manually from 1857 to the 1960s to guide boats through the bay . 
  The island has to be reached by boat and can be hired for the return trip for €100 (£70)